but white has a strong idea that disrupts his plans:} 13. Ne4 $1 {[%cal Ge4d6]}
Nxe4 14. Qxe4 {[%cal Ge4a8] making sure black can never play Bb7.} Rb8 15. dxc5
$1 Nxc5 16. Qd4 f6 $16 {[%csl Gb2,Gc4,Rd6,Re6][%cal Gf1d1,Gb2a3] all this was
forced in 1/2-1/2 Teofilovic,V (2125)-Bukal,V (2400)/Zagreb 1998/CBM 062 Extra
(41) White's pressure is very strong.}) 11. c5 {Of course.} Bc7 12. b4 h6 $6 {
This is pointless.} (12... a5 13. a3 e5 {made more sense and then} 14. dxe5
Nxe5 15. Nxe5 Bxe5 16. Ne2 $14 {[%csl Rb7,Rc6,Gd4] gives white a typical edge
in this line. It is important to note that the classical bishop sacrifice does
not work here} Bxh2+ 17. Kxh2 Ng4+ {because of} 18. Kg3 Qg5 19. Bxh7+ Kh8 20.
f4 $18) 13. a4 Qe7 14. Ne2 e5 15. dxe5 Nxe5 16. Nxe5 Bxe5 17. Bxe5 Qxe5 18. h3
{[%csl Gg4][%cal Rf6g4]} Rfb8 19. Nd4 $16 {This is just a nightmare position
for black if you play against Petrosian. I suggest the reader to see the rest
