wants after} 19. Bxh6 $36 {[%csl Gb3,Gf5,Rg8,Gh6]}) 19. Nxd5 Nxd5 {[%csl Gb3,
Gd2,Gf5][%cal Ge1e8] If you turn on your engine, it will give you an
evaluation around equal, but if you ask any experienced player whether he
would take white or black here, I believe the percentage would be high in
white's favor. The part of the game that modern engines still do not fully
appreciate is the attacking potential of a certain position. Here it clearly
underestimates white's chances, so let us see how white can create initiative
"out of a thin air".} 20. Re4 {[%csl Ge4][%cal Ge4g4]} (20. h4 $5 Qd6 21. g3 g6
$6 (21... Qd7 $142) 22. Qf3 h5 23. Re5 $1 $36 {[%csl Ge5][%cal Ge5h5,Ge1e5]}
