Nxd4 {[%cal Gd4f5]} Ne5 {[%csl Rf5][%cal Gc8f5,Ge5c4] we get a typical
position for this line. Where should the bishop go?} 14. Bf1 $1 {[%csl Gf1]
[%cal Gg2g3,Gf1g2] An excellent prophylactic move. Black wants to play c6-c5
in some lines and thus the bishop is best positioned out of harm's way on f1.
Also, white can later re-deploy it via g2.} Rd8 {A sensible move.} ({
Immediately} 14... c5 15. Nde2 Nc6 16. Bg5 $36 {[%cal Gf2f4,Gc3d5] is very
